special_powers.name: BAT TRICKS

special_powers.description: Superboy can use Poison, Pulse Wave, and Telekinesis.

special_powers.name: HEADSTRONG
special_powers.description: Wonder Girl can use Charge. When she does, she can use Improved Movement: Characters, Destroy Blocking.

special_powers.name: REACTIVE ARMOR
special_powers.description: When Wonder Girl has no action tokens, she can use Impervious. When Wonder Girl has 1 action token, she can use Invulnerability. When Wonder Girl has 2 action tokens, she can use Toughness.

special_powers.name: MISCOMMUNICATION & MISDIRECTION
special_powers.description: Give Red Hood a free action and choose a character within 6 squares. That character can't use Outwit until your next turn. If that character possesses the Batman Ally or Batman Enemy team ability, they can't use that team ability until your next turn.

special_powers.name: COMBINED FIREPOWER
special_powers.description: Give N.O.W.H.E.R.E. Soldier a power action and choose an adjacent friendly character. This turn, the chosen character modifies its damage value by +1 while adjacent to this character and making a ranged combat attack.

special_powers.name: MINION: FOR BLOOD
special_powers.description: If a friendly character named Brother Blood is within 8 squares, Brother Blood Acolyte can use Posion and Willpower, he may choose that damage dealt is penetrating damage; If you do, deal Brother Blood Acolyte 1 unavoidable damage after actions resolve.

special_powers.name: NO PROMISE THIS IS GOING TO WORK
special_powers.description: Give Solstice a power action and choose a square within her range that is on a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal path from her. All objects, walls, or squares of blocking terrain that would hinder or block line of fire to that square are destroyed.

special_powers.name: DARKNESS & LIGHT
special_powers.description: When Solstice has no action tokens, lines of fire can't be drawn to her when it is not your turn. If the line of fire for a ranged attack targeting Solstice crosses through hindering terrain, modify her defense by an additional +1.

special_powers.name: SUBJECT 8: ACTIVATED
special_powers.description: Rose Wilson begins the game on her green starting line. Any adjacent character may be given a power action to click Rose Wilson 6 clicks to the right.

special_powers.name: TWO SWORDS, FEW WORDS
special_powers.description: Rose Wilson can use Charge and Flurry.

special_powers.name: RELENTLESS DEFENSE
special_powers.description: Rose Wilson can use Combat Reflexes. When she is the target of a close combat attack, she can use Super Senses.

special_powers.name: PSIONIC COILS
special_powers.description: Leash can use Plasticity.

special_powers.name: YOU'RE A PART OF ME
special_powers.description: Leash can use Incapacitate and Telekinesis.

special_powers.name: TRANSPORT COILS
special_powers.description: Give Leash a close combat action that deals no damage and targets all adjacent opposing characters; if he hits any opposing characters, Leash may be placed anywhere within his speed value and may place one hit character adjacent to himself.

special_powers.name: ANGER, I CAN WORK WITH THAT
special_powers.description: Grymm can use Mind Control. When he does, modify his attack value by +2 and he may target opposing characters with Battle Fury.

special_powers.name: PARALYTIC TOXIC
special_powers.description: Grymm can use Poison. When he does, you may give characters of 150 points or less an action token instead of being dealt damage.

special_powers.name: GENETIC IMPLANT
special_powers.description: Grymm can use Super Senses. When he does and evades an attack, deal the attacker 1 damage.

special_powers.name: WHERE DO YOU THINK YOUR POWER COMES FROM?
special_powers.description: Each time an opposing character with the Mystical keyword or Mystics team ability targets Trigon with Probability Control, immediately modify his combat values by +1 until the beginning of your next turn.

special_powers.name: REALITY WARP
special_powers.description: Trigon can use Penetrating/Psychic Blast as if he had "2 targets". At the beginning of your turn, Trigon can use Barrier as a free action, he may only place two blocking terrain markers, each within his range and line of fire, but these markers do not need to be adjacent to each other. When these terrain markers are removed at the beginning of your turn, deal 1 damage to opposing characters adjacent to those markers' squares.

special_powers.name: JUST WHEN YOU THINK HE'S GONE...
special_powers.description: If this click is revealed when taking damage from an opponent's attack, stop turning the dial. Trigon can use Regeneration and Super Senses.

special_powers.name: DEMONIC DISRUPTION
special_powers.description: Trigon can use Perplex and Probability Control.
This character possesses Titans Team Ability. If this character already has Titans Team Ability, it can use the team ability as a free action.

This character can use Incapacitate and Outwit. When you use Outwit and actions resolve, if this character targets the same opposing character with Incapacitate, modify this character's attack value by +1. Give this character a power action and choose a power; that power is countered on all opposing characters within 5 squares. Give this character a double power action and choose a character within 10 squares and line of fire; deal that character 1 unavoidable damage and all of its powers and abilities are countered until your next turn.
This character can use Steal Energy, but is also healed when its ranged combat attack causes an opposing character to take damage.

special_powers.name: TITANS, TOGETHER FOREVER
special_powers.description: When all team members are attached, New Teen Titans can't be the target of Mind Control or Penetrating/Psychic Blast.

special_powers.name: TRAINING EVERY WEEKEND AT TITANS TOWER
special_powers.description: New Teen Titans can use Toughness and Combat Reflexes.

special_powers.name: NOT SIDEKICKS ANYMORE
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, choose one: Outwit, Perplex, or Probability Control. New Teen Titans can use that power this turn.

special_powers.name: CHANGLING
special_powers.description: New Teen Titans can use Shape Change.

special_powers.name: CYBORG
special_powers.description: New Teen Titans can't be the target of opposing character's Probability Control.

special_powers.name: KID FLASH
special_powers.description: New Teen Titans can use Hypersonic Speed and when they do, modify their speed value by +2.

special_powers.name: RAVEN
special_powers.description: When New Teen Titans are not adjacent to an opposing character, they can use Regeneration.

special_powers.name: ROBIN
special_powers.description: New Teen Titans can use Outwit and only adjacent characters can target them with Outwit.

special_powers.name: STARFIRE
special_powers.description: New Teen Titans can use Defend and the Flight ability.

special_powers.name: WONDER GIRL
special_powers.description: New Teen Titans can use Super Strength and the Flight ability.

special_powers.name: WE GO WHERE WE'RE NEEDED
special_powers.description: Give New Teen Titans a power action and place them adjacent to the highest point opposing character, then make a close combat attack as a free action.

special_powers.name: THE FOUNDING MEMBERS
special_powers.description: When all team members are attached, Justice League's powers and abilities can't be countered.

special_powers.name: WATCHTOWER
special_powers.description: At the beginning of the game, choose a team ability or keyword possessed by a character on the opposing team. Opposing characters with that team ability or keyword can't use Stealth.

special_powers.name: TRUTH AND JUSTICE
special_powers.description: Opposing characters within 4 squares can't have their combat values modified if the modified result would be higher than the original.

special_powers.name: WE DEPEND ON EACH OTHER
special_powers.description: Justice League can use Defend, Super Senses, and Toughness.

special_powers.name: AQUAMAN
special_powers.description: Justice League ignores Shape Change and their attacks can't be evaded.

special_powers.name: BATMAN
special_powers.description: Opposing characters within 5 squares of Justice League can't use Perplex.

special_powers.name: CYBORG
special_powers.description: Justice League can use the Sharpshooter ability and modifies their range value by +2.

special_powers.name: THE FLASH
special_powers.description: Opposing characters using Hypersonic Speed modify their attack and damage values by -1.

special_powers.name: GREEN LANTERN
special_powers.description: Justice League can use Barrier and Telekinesis.

special_powers.name: SUPERMAN
special_powers.description: Damage dealt to Justice League is reduced by 1 in addition to any other effects.

special_powers.name: WONDER WOMAN
special_powers.description: Justice League can use Energy Shield/Deflection.

special_powers.name: SAVING THE WORLD
special_powers.description: Justice League can use Colossal Stamina.

special_powers.name: THE CONTRACT
special_powers.description: Titans: Villains for Hire can use the Sharpshooter ability. At the beginning of the game choose an opposing character; that character is The Mark. If The Mark is KO'd by an attack made by a character with the Villains for Hire keyword victory points awarded for that character are doubled.

special_powers.name: STRIKING FROM THE SHADOWS
special_powers.description: Titans: Villains for Hire can use Running Shot and Stealth.

special_powers.name: ALWAYS RETURN FOR THE KILL
special_powers.description: Titans: Villains for Hire can use Toughness and Regeneration.

special_powers.name: CHESHIRE
special_powers.description: Titans: Villains for Hire can use Poison. When they do, damage dealt to The Mark is penetrating damage.

special_powers.name: CINDER
special_powers.description: Titans: Villains for Hire can use Phasing/Teleport. Lines of fire drawn by Titans: Villains for Hire to The Mark ignore blocking terrain.

special_powers.name: DEATHSTROKE
special_powers.description: Titans: Villains for Hire can use Outwit. When Titans Villains for Hire attack the Mark modify their attack and damage values by +1.

special_powers.name: OSIRIS
special_powers.description: Titans: Villains for Hire can use Charge. After Titans: Villains for Hire resolve a move action, if they are adjacent to The Mark, you may give them a close combat action as a free action.

special_powers.name: TATTOOED MAN
special_powers.description: Titans: Villains for Hire can use Shape Change. When Titans: Villains for Hire are attacked by The Mark, they succeed for Shape Change on a result of 4 - 6.

special_powers.name: LEARNING TO FIGHT BACK
special_powers.description: If Gen13 was attacked last turn, their damage value is locked this turn and any damage dealt by them is penetrating damage.

special_powers.name: BURNOUT
special_powers.description: Gen13 can use Pulse Wave.

special_powers.name: FAIRCHILD
special_powers.description: Gen13 can use Super Strength.

special_powers.name: FREEFALL
special_powers.description: Gen13 can use Force Blast and Telekinesis.

special_powers.name: GRUNGE
special_powers.description: Gen13 can use the Move and Attack ability.

special_powers.name: SARAH RAINMAKER
special_powers.description: Gen13 can use Energy Explosion with 3 targets.

special_powers.name: WE'RE THE NEXT GENERATION
special_powers.description: Gen13 can use Perplex twice per turn. When they do, they may only target themselves once per turn.

special_powers.name: FULL ROSTER
special_powers.description: When all characters are attached to Teen Titans, Teen Titans can use Colossal Stamina.

special_powers.name: WE CREATED A FAMILY
special_powers.description: Teen Titans can use Energy Shield/Deflection, Super Senses and Toughness.

special_powers.name: AQUALAD
special_powers.description: Teen Titans can't have their combat values modified by opposing characters.

special_powers.name: KID FLASH
special_powers.description: Teen Titans can use Hypersonic Speed and when they do, modify their speed value by +2.

special_powers.name: ROBIN
special_powers.description: Teen Titans can use Outwit and only adjacent characters can target them with Outwit.

special_powers.name: WONDER GIRL
special_powers.description: Teen Titans can use the Flight ability and ignore Shape Change.

special_powers.name: TITANS TOGETHER!
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, roll a d6. On a result of 5-6, remove an action token from Teen Titans.

special_powers.name: WE GOT ALONG FINE ON OUR OWN
special_powers.description: Outlaws may have as few as 2 team members attached. Outlaws can use Sharpshooter ability.

special_powers.name: ALL TOGETHER NOW!
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, choose Combat Reflexes or Super Senses. Outlaws can use the chosen power until next turn when all members of this team dial are attached.

special_powers.name: ARSENAL
special_powers.description: Outlaws can use Energy Explosion, Energy Shield/Deflection and Incapacitate.

special_powers.name: RED HOOD
special_powers.description: Outlaws can use Combat Reflexes, Leap/Climb and Stealth.

special_powers.name: STARFIRE
special_powers.description: Outlaws can use Poison and Toughness. Outlaws have "wing transporter" symbol.

special_powers.name: SHOOT FIRST, ASK QUESTIONS LATER
special_powers.description: If Outlaws are given the first non-free action of the turn, damage dealt is penetrating damage for that action. Outlaws can use Outwit but only as the last action of the turn.
Orange squares are Lava Squares. At the end of each player's turn, deal 1 unavoidable damage to each character occupying a Lava Square.
